Landon Donovan admitted his international send-off was ‘beyond his wildest dreams’after his 157th and final match for the USA.

The American star was given a testimonial to sign off his career after being left out of Jurgen Klinsmann's World Cup squad.

But the 32-year-old said he never expected to play for his country again after the snub, and paid credit to US Soccer president Sunil Gulati for making it happen. 

